President Jacob Zuma will deliver the statement at the Orlando Stadium on Sunday following this week's National Executive Committee meeting. JOHANNESBURG African National Congress (ANC) Treasurer-General Zweli Mkhize says tensions within the ruling party and efforts to stamp out factionalism will be among the issues dealt with in the party's 8 January statement this weekend.President Jacob Zuma will deliver the statement at the Orlando Stadium on Sunday following this week's National Executive Committee (NEC) meeting.During last year's meeting, several members tried to bring a resolution to remove Zuma from the presidency.Mkhize says issues of job creation and economic growth will be discussed on Sunday as well as issues of unity. The issue that all of us have been aware of inside the ANC has been the issue of tensions and factions. All of these issues are pulling leader toward the national conference. (Edited by Tamsin Wort)